commit.message:
Release 2.0.1

* Update README and setup.py with new release information.
* Add Py3.8 to trove classifiers in setup.py, while we're at it.

Allow trailing commas in arrays and lists

This is allowed by the libconfig grammar, but was wrongly flagged as a
syntax error by python-libconf.

Fixes #18

Release 2.0.0

* Update README and setup.py with new release information.
* Update trove classifiers in setup.py, while we're at it.

Fix travis configuration

* Rework travis config to use tox-travis
* Python3.7 requires dist: xenial / sudo: yes;
  cf. https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-ci/issues/9815

Validate output on dump()/dumps()

Make sure that libconfig files written with this library can be read
by the C/C++ reference implementation.

* Raise ConfigSerializeError when writing invalid libconfig arrays
* Add the possibility to write libconfig 64bit-Integer values

Closes: #15

Merge branch 'AnandTella/DeepCopyAttrDict'

Fix a problem with AttrDict that surfaced with deepcopy, hasattr, and
OrderedDict's.
Update tox and travis configs for Py3.6/3.7

DeepCopy AttrDict fails

  - The "__getattr__" should raise AttributeError on KeyError

Raise the AttributeError on KeyError as expected by __getattr__

  - __getattr__ raises AttributeError and the __getitem__ raises
  KeyError
  - As __getattr__ is redirected to __getitem__ the exception has to be
  raised accordingly
  - This also works for the attribute _OrderedDict__root
  - Deepy copy calls getattr(x, "__deepcopy__", None) and fails if
  AttributeError is not raised on unavailable attributes

Py env variable py33 added

 - tox ci is failing as py33 env variable was missing

Raise the AttributeError on KeyError as expected by __getattr__

  - __getattr__ raises AttributeError and the __getitem__ raises
  KeyError
  - As __getattr__ is redirected to __getitem__ the exception has to be
  raised accordingly
  - This also works for the attribute _OrderedDict__root
  - Deepy copy calls getattr(x, "__deepcopy__", None) and fails if
  AttributeError is not raised on unavailable attributes
Release 1.0.1

Optimize performance

Parsing large files was very slow. Two optimizations were made:
* Stop copying the input string in Tokenizer.tokenize()
  The string slicing caused copying of the whole input string on every
  token. Now, weexplicitly track our position in the string and pass that
  to the regex functions, leaving the string untouched.
  This was the big one and sped up execution by a factor of 5.4.
* Optimize the order in which the parser checks tokens if multiple token
  types are possible. This gave an additional speedup of 12%.

Overall, the parsing time of a 1MB file went from 91 to 15 seconds. More
optimizations would definitely be possible, but they are less obvious than
the string copying issue.
Make parsing regexes more readable

Use io.open() in README.rst example

python-libconf requires unicode input. This implies using io.open() on
Python 2.7. Fix the example to reflect this.

Handle names that start with true or false

I found out that parsing of names like "true_value", "falseVal" was
broken, as the first characters were interpreted as boolean values.

Change the regex for bools so it only matches for "standalone" true/false.
Release 1.0.0

Use OrderedDict to maintain config entry order

Preserve the order of config entries when loading libconfig data by making
AttrDict a subclass of collections.OrderedDict.

Sanitize and document bytes/unicode handling

When writing libconf files, escape unprintable characters below 0x80, pass
all other characters through as-is.

When reading libconf files, decode all escape sequences, pass everything
else through as-is.

Document the recommended way to handle encoding issues in README.rst.
Coding style and tox updates to make flake8 happy

Merge dump() implementation from 'clarkli86-master'

Closes #2.

Refactor dump() logic prior to merge

* Improve README.rst wording
* Remove `builtins` import, it's unnecessary and causes problems on 2.7
* Escape strings before dump()ing them
* Remove code duplication in the dump() logic
* Rename ConfigSerialiseError to ConfigSerializeError (American
  spelling) because the rest of the codebase uses AE as well.

Make floating point regex more lenient

Allow numbers such as "1E10" to be parsed as floats.
Closes #3 on GitHub.
Fix whitespace issues in test_tokenize.py
Add basestring to builtins
Define more builtins
Add deps to tox
Install dependency in travis

Dump using StringIO

Fix flake8 style check

Handle big int
